HEADWORD: Branchiostegal
<hw>Bran`chi*os"te*gal</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
gill + <?/ to cover: cf. F. <ets>branchiost⟦egrave⟧ge</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to the membrane covering the gills of
fishes.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A
branchiostegal ray. See <xex>Illustration</xex> of <cref>Branchial
arches</cref> in Appendix.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This term was formerly applied to a group of fishes
having boneless branchi⟦ae⟧. But the arrangement was artificial, and has
been rejected.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Branchiostege</ent>⟦br⟧
